        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 6:42PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 642 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 10 miles west of Hayden to 18 miles
north of Tucumcari, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rosebud.

This includes State Road 104 between Mile Markers 96 and 101.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
